On Monday, Jasmine had 3 paperclips.
On Tuesday, she had 6.
On Wednesday, she had 6 * 2 = <<6*2=12>>12 paperclips.
On Thursday, she had 12 * 2 = <<12*2=24>>24 paperclips.
On Friday, she had 24 * 2 = <<24*2=48>>48 paperclips.
On Saturday, she had 48 * 2 = <<48*2=96>>96 paperclips.
On Sunday, she had 96 * 2 = <<96*2=192>>192 paperclips.

Jasmine first had more than 100 paperclips on Sunday. Answer: \boxed{\text{Sunday}}.
